</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D4DCF5923C551454A28DFE13FDA5FCF6" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="9C79A6193C551454A28DFE13FDA5FCF6" blockId="2.[151,1436,428,868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A28DFE13FE96FD9B" box="[199,343,497,521]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Schreiteriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A28DFE13FE96FD9B" box="[199,343,497,521]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Schreiteriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was suggested as an objective replacement name for 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A1D5FE13FA59FD9B" authority="Dyar, 1937 (Fletcher &amp; Nye 1982)" authorityName="Dyar, 1937 (Fletcher &amp; Nye" authorityYear="1982" box="[927,1432,497,521]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schreiteria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A1D5FE13FBD5FD9B" box="[927,1044,497,521]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Schreiteria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F857DBE83C551454A657FE10FB54FD9B" author="Dyar" box="[1053,1173,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refString="Dyar, H. S. (1937) Cossidae In: Seitz, A. (Ed.), Die exotischen Großschmetterlinge, Die amerikanischen Spinner und Schwarmer, Stuttgart: Alfred Kernen, pp. 1265 - 1285." type="book chapter" year="1937">Dyar, 1937</bibRefCitation>
(Fletcher &amp; Nye 1982)
</taxonomicName>
. The monotypic 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A306FDF6FE00FDBE" box="[332,449,532,556]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schreiteria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A306FDF6FE00FDBE" box="[332,449,532,556]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Schreiteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established for 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A0F8FDF6FB8AFDBE" authority="Dyar, 1937" authorityName="Dyar" authorityYear="1937" box="[690,1099,532,556]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schreiteria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinicornis">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A0F8FDF6FC7EFDBE" box="[690,959,532,556]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Schreiteria pectinicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F857DBE83C551454A186FDF7FB8AFDBE" author="Dyar" box="[972,1099,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refString="Dyar, H. S. (1937) Cossidae In: Seitz, A. (Ed.), Die exotischen Großschmetterlinge, Die amerikanischen Spinner und Schwarmer, Stuttgart: Alfred Kernen, pp. 1265 - 1285." type="book chapter" year="1937">Dyar, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but it proved to be a junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A363FDD5FDF4FDDD" authority="Melzer, 1933" authorityName="Melzer" authorityYear="1933" box="[297,565,567,591]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schreiteria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A363FDD5FE5FFDDD" box="[297,414,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Schreiteria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F857DBE83C551454A3EDFDDAFDF4FDDD" author="Melzer" box="[423,565,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refString="Melzer, J. (1933) Nota previa sobre um longicornio interessante dos Andes da Argentina. Revista de Entomologia, 3, 459 - 461." type="journal article" year="1933">Melzer, 1933</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A00EFDDAFD7EFDDD" box="[580,703,568,591]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A080FDDAFCA6FDDD" box="[714,871,568,591]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cerambycidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A139FDDAFC1BFDDD" box="[883,986,568,591]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Lamiinae">Lamiinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A1ACFDDAFB98FDDD" box="[998,1113,568,591]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Parmenini">Parmenini</taxonomicName>
). 
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A626FDD5FB17FDDD" box="[1132,1238,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Shreiteria</emphasis>
Dyar, the original generic name for 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A31DFDB8FE23FDE3" box="[343,482,602,625]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schreiteria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinicornis">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A31DFDB8FE23FDE3" box="[343,482,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">pectinicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was included in the Key to the 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A102FDB8FC7FFDE3" box="[840,958,602,625]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Zeuzerinae">Zeuzerinae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="F857DBE83C551454A1A3FDB8FBA8FDE3" author="Dyar" box="[1001,1129,602,625]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refString="Dyar, H. S. (1937) Cossidae In: Seitz, A. (Ed.), Die exotischen Großschmetterlinge, Die amerikanischen Spinner und Schwarmer, Stuttgart: Alfred Kernen, pp. 1265 - 1285." type="book chapter" year="1937">Dyar (1937</bibRefCitation>
: 1265). 
<bibRefCitation id="F857DBE83C551454A688FDB8FA5AFDE3" author="Schoorl" box="[1218,1435,602,625]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refString="Schoorl, J. W. (1990) A phylogenetic study on Cossidae (Lepidoptera: Ditrysia) based on external adult morphology. Zoologische Ferhandelingen, 263, 1 ‾ 295." type="journal article" year="1990">Schoorl (1990: 227)</bibRefCitation>
calls into question the placement of 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A052FD9EFD69FD06" box="[536,680,636,660]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Schreiteriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A052FD9EFD69FD06" box="[536,680,636,660]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Schreiteriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A0B8FD9FFC97FD06" box="[754,854,637,660]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cossidae</taxonomicName>
. As an argument, Schoorl gives the peculiarities of the thorax structure of the syntype 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A3B0FD7DFC51FD25" authority="Dyar, 1937" authorityName="Dyar" authorityYear="1937" box="[506,912,671,695]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schreiteria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinicornis">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A3B0FD7DFCC7FD25" box="[506,774,671,695]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Schreiteria pectinicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F857DBE83C551454A158FD42FC51FD25" author="Dyar" box="[786,912,672,695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refString="Dyar, H. S. (1937) Cossidae In: Seitz, A. (Ed.), Die exotischen Großschmetterlinge, Die amerikanischen Spinner und Schwarmer, Stuttgart: Alfred Kernen, pp. 1265 - 1285." type="book chapter" year="1937">Dyar, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Citation: “The thorax of 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A6F3FD42FA85FD25" box="[1209,1348,672,695]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schreiteria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinicornis">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A6F3FD42FA85FD25" box="[1209,1348,672,695]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">pectinicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to that in 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A31AFD23FDD9FD4B" authority="The" authorityName="The" box="[336,536,705,729]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Cossula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A31AFD23FDD9FD4B" box="[336,536,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Cossula magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
… The mesepimeron lacks a pale band. The male retinaculum has a very long base. The uncus is broad and gradually rounded. Because of these differences, especially the type of mesepimeron, 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A2DDFCE5FEE6FC8D" box="[151,295,775,799]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Schreiteriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A2DDFCE5FEE6FC8D" box="[151,295,775,799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Schreiteriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is excluded from the 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A047FCEAFDB3FC8D" box="[525,626,776,799]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cossidae</taxonomicName>
”. 
<bibRefCitation id="F857DBE83C551454A0CCFCEAFCADFC8D" box="[646,876,776,799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refString="Edwards, E. D., Gentili, P., Horak, M., Kristensen, N. P. &amp; Nielsen, E. S. (1999) The Cossoid / Sesoid Assemblage In: Kristensen, N. P. (Ed.), Lepidoptera, Moths and Butterflies. Folume 1: Evolution, Systematics, and Biogeography. Handbuch der Zoologie, Berlin, New York, pp. 188 ‾ 197." type="journal article">Edwards et al. (1999)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="F857DBE83C551454A1D4FCEAFBA6FC8D" box="[926,1127,776,799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refString="Davis, S. R., Gentili-Poole, P. &amp; Mitter, C. H. (2008) A revision of the Cossulinae of Costa Rica and cladistic analysis of the world species (Lepidoptera: Cossidae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 154, 222 ‾ 277. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2008.00406. x" type="journal article">Davis et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, clearly states problems with Schoorl’s choice of characters across his study. The study of genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A1E8FCC8FB16FCD3" authority="Dyar, 1937" authorityName="Dyar" authorityYear="1937" box="[930,1239,810,833]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schreiteria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinicornis">
<emphasis id="AEB27A0B3C551454A1E8FCC8FB87FCD3" box="[930,1094,810,833]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">S. pectinicornis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F857DBE83C551454A61FFCC8FB0EFCD3" author="Dyar" box="[1109,1231,810,833]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refString="Dyar, H. S. (1937) Cossidae In: Seitz, A. (Ed.), Die exotischen Großschmetterlinge, Die amerikanischen Spinner und Schwarmer, Stuttgart: Alfred Kernen, pp. 1265 - 1285." type="book chapter" year="1937">Dyar, 1937</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
indicated that this taxon belongs to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="5BC6DD9A3C551454A3ACFCAFFDA1FCF6" box="[486,608,845,868]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Zeuzerinae">Zeuzerinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
